Subject: [PATCH] tools/vm/slabinfo-gnuplot: use "grep -E" instead of "egrep"
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.0.12
Git-commit: a435874bf626f55d7147026b059008c8de89fbb8

commit a435874bf626f55d7147026b059008c8de89fbb8 upstream.

The latest version of grep claims the egrep is now obsolete so the build
now contains warnings that look like:

	egrep: warning: egrep is obsolescent; using grep -E

fix this up by moving the related file to use "grep -E" instead.

  sed -i "s/egrep/grep -E/g" `grep egrep -rwl tools/vm`

Here are the steps to install the latest grep:

  wget http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/grep/grep-3.8.tar.gz
  tar xf grep-3.8.tar.gz
  cd grep-3.8 && ./configure && make
  sudo make install
  export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH

